Mission Name: AIES-BSMC I

Launcher: AIES-BSMC Type A

Payload: Manned Orbiter

Manned/Unmanned: Manned

Mission Objective: Launch a manned orbiter into orbit and back with AIES parts

Mission Outcome: Success! (Yet killed a kerbal)

Mission Highlights/Pictures:

Lift Off!

Mission Name: AIES-BSMC II

Launcher: AIES-BSMC type A

Payload: ScienceSat

Manned/Unmanned: Unmanned

Mission Objective: Launch ScienceSat into Orbit

Mission Outcome: Success!

Mission Status: In LKO

Mission Highlights/Pictures:

ScienceSat in orbit
Nice Sat, Hopefully Galileo Space Age.... [Classified] Can get [Classified] to [Classified]

Thank you.

(Next mission report in a few minutes)

Mission Name: AIES-BSMC III

Launcher: AIES-BSMC Type A

Payload: MapSat

Manned/Unmanned: Unmanned

Mission Objective: Launch a mapping sattelite into orbit for the ISSO

Mission Outcome: Success!

Mission Status: In LKO

Mission Highlights/Pictures:

MapSat in orbit

Mission Name: AIES-BSMC IV

Launcher: AIES-BSMC Type A

Payload: Manned Science Orbiter with Jebidiah

Manned/Unmanned: Manned

Mission Objective: Launch a Manned Orbiter with science equipment into orbit and return

Mission Outcome: Failure! Stranded Jeb in space due to absence of parachutes

Mission Status: In LKO

Mission Highlights/Pictures:

Stranded

Mission Name: AIES-BSMC V

Launcher: AIES-BSMC Type A4L

Payload: Solar Satellite

Manned/Unmanned: Unmanned

Mission Objective: Launch a sattelite into solar orbit.

Mission Outcome: Failure! Burnt up in atmosphere!

Mission Highlights/Pictures:

The satellite burning up

Mission Name: AIES-BSMC VI

Launcher: AIES-BSMC A6S

Payload: Low Kerbin Orbital Space Station

Manned/Unmanned: Manned

Mission Objective: Launch a space station into space

Mission Outcome: Catostrophic Failure! 2 kerbals KIA

Mission Highlights/Pictures:

The payload/launcher breaking up after an abort to orbit attempt
Lol, To public, I see a Montage of Nasa i my head right now.

Mission Name: AIES-BSMC VII

Launcher: AIES-BSMC Type A6S

Payload: LKOSS

Manned/Unmanned: Manned

Mission Objective: Launch the Low Kerbin Orbital Space Station

Mission Outcome: Major Success! Not a single anomly. 2 debris left in orbit.

Mission Status: In orbit.
